title: @OspreyWSOC Heads to JU for Annual River City Rumble
text: 5' 9" Fr. JACKSONVILLE, Fla. â€“ The North Florida Women's Soccer team travels to Jacksonville in their final regular-season contest this Friday at 7 p.m. in the annual River City Rumble at Southern Oak Stadium. "We have had a good week of training and are ready and excited to play," says coach . "JU has had a good run of results in the last couple of games. They have only given up four goals in conference play and we know they will be organized defensively." The Ospreys (4-10-1, 2-3-1 A-Sun) sit in a tie for fifth place in the A-Sun entering the final match of conference play. They look to clinch a spot in the conference tournament. The Dolphins (5-7-2, 3-2-1 A-Sun) are in a tie for third place and have clinched a spot in the tournament. North Florida is coming off of a tough weekend on the road. Last Friday, the Ospreys fell 2-1 to Kennesaw State on a late goal, before playing USC Upstate to a 0-0 draw last Sunday.
